The Best Hit

2
00:00:01,620 --> 00:00:05,300
♫ The stars floating in the night sky ♫

3
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:08,410
♫ Twinkle even more today ♫

4
00:00:08,410 --> 00:00:11,620
♫ Like your eyes, like your lips ♫

5
00:00:11,620 --> 00:00:14,130
Yoon Si Yoon 
♫ They make my heart flutter  ♫

6
00:00:14,130 --> 00:00:16,800
Yoon Si Yoon 
♫ Beautiful day  ♫

7
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,800
Lee Se Young 
♫ And I have something to say ♫

8
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,600
Kim Min Jae
♫ Something to tell ♫

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:25,130
Cha Tae Hyun 
♫ I wanna shout out your name to the sky ♫

10
00:00:25,130 --> 00:00:28,400
♫ I’ll tell you ♫

11
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:33,070
♫ I love you ♫

12
00:00:33,070 --> 00:00:35,970
♫ It’s a beautiful day ♫

13
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,810
Anyway, she's always pretending to be doing something all alone,

14
00:00:40,810 --> 00:00:45,200
but every day she is so clumsy and keeps spilling something over.

15
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,480
Then you should stay here for a bit.

16
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:57,670
Hey, you. What are you doing here, like this?

17
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,770
Wow. Why did you drink so much?

18
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:04,610
Ah, what should I do?

19
00:01:13,780 --> 00:01:15,320
Bo Hee?

20
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:20,750
Hey! You jerk!

21
00:01:24,410 --> 00:01:26,670
You better let go of Bo Hee!

22
00:01:33,290 --> 00:01:37,390
Gwang Jae. It's me, Yoo Hyeon Jae.

23
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:41,400
You don't believe this, right? Right, I can't believe this.

24
00:01:42,820 --> 00:01:44,750
It's driving you crazy, right?

25
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:50,160
If I put myself in you shoes, I think I'd feel the same way.

26
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:56,830
I didn't know when I saw you from afar, but from close up, you're old. You aged a lot.

27
00:01:56,830 --> 00:02:01,390
Is the hair of your head okay? You were always so worried about losing hair because of your dad's baldness.

28
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:05,120
You used to eat black sesame seeds and get a massage for your scalp—

29
00:02:05,770 --> 00:02:06,910
What's wrong with you?

30
00:02:06,910 --> 00:02:11,900
So... Tell me again who you are.

31
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:14,910
It's me, Yoo Hyeon Jae.

32
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,490
Hey, does that make sense?

33
00:02:16,490 --> 00:02:21,520
It doesn't make sense. I know it makes no sense. But that's what just happened.

34
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:36,610
You're right, Gwang Jae. It's hard to believe but I'm back.

35
00:02:36,610 --> 00:02:38,450
Ta-da!

36
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,900
You, why did you all of a sudden?

37
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:47,800
No matter how much I think about it, I can't believe you.

38
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,280
Give me proof that you're the real Hyeon Jae.

39
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:53,440
How can I do that? I left my ID and everything back then.

40
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:56,860
Also, would you believe me if I showed you my ID in this situation? You wouldn't.

41
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:59,890
What's your name? Not Yoo Hyeon Jae. Your birth name. Your real name.

42
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:01,300
Bong Jae. Yoo Bong Jae.

43
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:06,140
No, no. If you search that on the internet, it comes out easily.

44
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:10,800
Right. Hyeon Jae, that name. When, where and who made that name for you?

45
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:14,770
That name... It was Chairman Soon who got it from a fortune-teller.

46
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:18,640
But, I didn't like it. So I changed it and ended up calling myself Yoo Hyeon Jae.

47
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:22,720
Oh, I'm right. How many years have you been working with me and you don't even know it's me?

48
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:25,000
I knew it was you the moment I saw you.

49
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:28,860
You look straight into my eyes.

50
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:36,440
Please stop already! I said I'm Hyeon Jae.

51
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:42,870
You punk. If you're the real Hyeon Jae, you'll have a scar on your ankle right now.

52
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:48,390
When you were a kid, you stepped on a hot pot and you got a burn scar. It was a star-shaped scar...

53
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,470
Do you believe me now?

54
00:03:56,490 --> 00:03:58,690
Then, you are the real one.

55
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:02,850
Right. It's me. I'm Hyeon Jae. Lee Hyeon Jae.

56
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:06,300
Come here.

57
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,330
♫ Oh, no, no ♫

58
00:04:18,150 --> 00:04:20,700
♫ After a long night passes ♫

59
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:25,910
I heard everything. But, you can't solve this problem by running away.

60
00:04:25,910 --> 00:04:28,630
Gwang Jae.

61
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:32,310
Thank you for coming after me.

62
00:04:32,310 --> 00:04:36,010
I thought I would leave without seeing your face. But, it's nice to see it.

63
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:40,260
Please send my greetings to Chairman. And when I get there—

64
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:44,190
Why are you running away? What did you do wrong to get away?!

65
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:45,800
You just liked someone.

66
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:49,980
Because people do like him and you just happened to like that person, is that something to run away for?

67
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,550
Everyone likes someone. That's what everyone does!

68
00:04:51,550 --> 00:04:55,660
I don't know where Hyeon Jae disappeared to but forget him.

69
00:04:55,660 --> 00:05:00,100
You can register Hyeon Jae's child as my son. I'll take responsibility.

70
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:02,420
And you can come back again!

71
00:05:02,420 --> 00:05:03,560
How can I do that to you?

72
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,680
- How can you put that burden on you?
- Just do as I say!

73
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:10,400
From now on, I'll protect you. I'll do that.

74
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:14,060
If you want to run away and hide somewhere to avoid it, don't go anywhere else.

75
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:15,610
Just come to me.

76
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:20,200
If people condemn you, I'll deal with anyone who says anything!

77
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,780
- Why would you?
- Because I'm Hyeon Jae's manager.

78
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,350
Hyeon Jae's business is my business.

79
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:28,140
Whatever Hyeon Jae did, I'll take full responsibility for that.

80
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:31,630
From now on, I'll take Hyeon Jae's place instead.

81
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:36,050
♫ Light in the sky ♫

82
00:05:36,050 --> 00:05:39,340
♫  The sky of my youth ♫

83
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:43,380
Right. It's me. I'm Hyeon Jae. Lee Hyeon Jae.

84
00:05:43,430 --> 00:05:45,800
♫  My dreams that I always wanted ♫

85
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,410
Come here.

86
00:05:47,410 --> 00:05:52,540
♫  Some day, fly fly fly ♫

87
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:00,910
I knew you were short-tempered, but how can you hit me so many times every time I say something?

88
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:04,900
So... To help me make sense of this nonsense, let's summarize it.

89
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:09,170
There was a typhoon, and you slid down your studio's stairs.

90
00:06:09,170 --> 00:06:12,480
When you woke up, 20 years had passed. Is that so?

91
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,990
- That's right.
- That makes no sense at all!

92
00:06:14,990 --> 00:06:19,600
No matter how absurd it may be, you should say something that makes it sound possible to some extent.

93
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,980
How do you think I feel when I say something that doesn't make sense?

94
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:24,250
You didn't just return from hiding somewhere else?

95
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:27,890
You just felt embarrassed to just return, so you made up a strange crap.

96
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:28,960
Am I that type of person?

97
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:31,600
You would do even more than that.

98
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:35,750
Then... The man Chairman saw the other day was...

99
00:06:36,690 --> 00:06:41,400
Oh, that. I just happened to meet him on the rooftop. I was also really surprised.

100
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:44,220
So that means you've been near us?

101
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:47,340
Not near you, but above you to be exact.

102
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:48,400
Above?

103
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:51,600
I live on the rooftop in my old studio.

104
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:55,470
What? Then what about Ji Hoon?

105
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:59,620
Don't worry. Your son doesn't even know who I am.

106
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:05,600
Anyway, Lee Gwang Jae, I thought you were a cruel guy.

107
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:10,480
When did you and Bo Hee get together?

108
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,910
Bo Hee originally used to like me.

109
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:13,310
You, really!

110
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:16,760
I'm Hyeon Jae. I won't get hit a third time.

111
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:26,810
Hey. Don't you know that the face is important to a celebrity? Why would you hit me in the face?

112
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:31,080
Now that I think about it, I'm a little sad.

113
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:35,820
Anyway, you're seeing me for the first time in nearly 20 years.

114
00:07:35,820 --> 00:07:39,040
You met your friend after 20 years, aren't you happy to see me at all?

115
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,210
Do you think I would be happy to see you?

116
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:48,190
Is it because of the loan? I heard about the building.

117
00:07:48,190 --> 00:07:50,330
Hey, so why would you leave and try so hard—

118
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:52,600
Be quiet. Don't you know it's all because of you?

119
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:57,300
What did I do? Right. I can understand why Chairman Soon Tae is a little upset at me.

120
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:59,590
So that's totally understandable. I think that's possible.

121
00:07:59,590 --> 00:08:02,050
But, why are you so upset at me?

122
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:03,700
Forget it.

123
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,070
Like you said, let's just pretend you're the real Yoo Hyeon Jae.

124
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,000
I'm not pretending—

125
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,610
Maybe you've been hiding somewhere for twenty hears and have just returned.

126
00:08:09,610 --> 00:08:13,140
Or as you say, you slid down the stairs and jumped 20 years into the future.

127
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:17,810
I don't care whatever it is, but listen to me carefully. I have only one thing to say to you.

128
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:19,000
What is it?

129
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,620
- Get lost.
- What?

130
00:08:20,620 --> 00:08:23,400
Don't disturb other people's lives who are already living well without you.

131
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,800
Just go back to where you came from quietly. Do you understand?!

132
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:33,140
Hey, what do you mean...

133
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:39,470
Ah, you really! How can I go back?

134
00:08:39,470 --> 00:08:42,130
I don't even know who I got here.

135
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:44,600
That jerk, why is he so mean to me?

136
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,520
Ah, that reminds me that I have to pick something. The bag.

137
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,270
Thumbs Up! Why are you back so late?

138
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:29,700
It was you, Lee Ji Hoon?

139
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,440
Why? You look disappointed to see me.

140
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,140
What disappointment?

141
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:37,520
By the way, did something happen earlier?

142
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:42,390
That's a long story to tell. Wait!

143
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:47,520
Lee Ji Hoon, it doesn't suit you, but were you worried about me by any chance?

144
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,700
Why would I be worried? That's not it.

145
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,600
Then, where are you coming from?

146
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:55,320
By any chance, are you dating behind my back?

147
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:57,550
What about dating? Can't I go on a date?

148
00:09:57,550 --> 00:10:00,600
Yes. Sure, you can.

149
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,930
- Are you really dating someone?
- I...

150
00:10:03,930 --> 00:10:07,240
Hey. How many times do I have to go back and forth? Here.

151
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:11,800
- Are you making a bag or what? What took you so long?
- Hey.

152
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,700
Why is your face like that?

153
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,160
I had a little business to take care of.

154
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,080
Where did you roll down?

155
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:20,550
Rolled down what? I said I had a little business to take care of.

156
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,710
You just came in too? You're late?

157
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:26,860
Why do you care?

158
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:38,100
Like father, like son. Why are they doing this to me?

159
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:42,050
The Best Hit

160
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,780
World Entertainment

161
00:11:12,890 --> 00:11:17,180
Hey, hey, this. It looks delicious.

162
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:22,690
Hey, hey. Why do we only have the head? Where is its body?

163
00:11:22,690 --> 00:11:27,810
It's fish head dark meat. It's said there are six flavors on the fish head.

164
00:11:27,810 --> 00:11:30,100
Do you mean fish-heads and animal-tails?

165
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:33,820
Well, it means fish heads are delicious and animal tails are too, right?

166
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:39,330
Right. The head of a fish is... As long as you know what I mean, then it's fine.

167
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:43,110
Aigoo. Ah, this is delicious.

168
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:45,700
It's so refreshing and delicious.

169
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:52,020
Ajumma. The fish keeps staring at me.

170
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,370
That's right, you did well.

171
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:02,240
From early in the morning, there is no need to start your day with a staring contest against a fish.

172
00:12:03,020 --> 00:12:07,280
I'm going to fry an egg and eat it with some rice.

173
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,870
Grandpa, I want it too.

174
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,410
Ji Hoon, do you want one too?

175
00:12:10,410 --> 00:12:13,340
- While you are at it, only if there is an extra egg.
- Okay.

176
00:12:17,310 --> 00:12:19,370
Aigoo. The taste is just fine.

177
00:12:19,370 --> 00:12:22,750
I think it's delicious. I like it.

178
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:30,200
The soup was so strange this morning, right?

179
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:33,920
What? No, it was delicious.

180
00:12:36,050 --> 00:12:39,260
I only knew how to eat, but I've never cooked before.

181
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:42,680
I don't know what I did to get this old that I don't even know how to cook.

182
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:45,020
I told you it was delicious.

183
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:55,100
By the way, last night I had a dream that I was with Hyeon Jae.

184
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:58,070
What?

185
00:12:58,690 --> 00:13:03,180
Aigoo. I think it's a dream. Does that make sense?

186
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:06,430
What?

187
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:12,400
No. Hyeon Jae said that he slid downstairs during a typhoon,

188
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:15,480
and after he woke up, he found out he came here 20 years later.

189
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:18,220
He said he came to where we're living.

190
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,920
That's a silly dream.

191
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:26,200
Right? It's a silly dream.

192
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:34,280
But, it didn't feel like a dream.

193
00:13:35,220 --> 00:13:39,500
It was as if Hyeon Jae came back.

194
00:13:53,570 --> 00:13:55,190
What?

195
00:13:55,190 --> 00:13:57,280
Are you all going somewhere?

196
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,400
Don't you have the day off?

197
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:01,770
We aren't a jobless bum like you.

198
00:14:01,770 --> 00:14:05,090
Hey, who is a jobless bum?

199
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:08,970
Hide until we come home. Don't get caught.

200
00:14:08,970 --> 00:14:11,890
- Don't spill stuff.
- Leave.

201
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:15,420
Hey, Lee Ji Hoon. Will you be home late today?

202
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:17,160
I don't know.

203
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:20,140
That guy, seriously!

204
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:21,710
What's wrong with him since this morning?

205
00:14:21,710 --> 00:14:25,050
Hey, why are you so tactless?

206
00:14:25,090 --> 00:14:27,810
Ji Hoon isn't feeling like himself lately.

207
00:14:27,810 --> 00:14:32,160
Isn't it because he failed to join the debut group? Why is he taking it out on me?

208
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:35,120
1,000,000 won

209
00:14:41,060 --> 00:14:46,030
First of all, should I buy some clothes?

210
00:14:46,030 --> 00:14:51,920
If I buy this and that, they could only cost 1000 won.

211
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:56,260
Should I get a room with the remaining money?

212
00:14:57,210 --> 00:15:01,610
No, no. It's better to stay here for now.

213
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:05,140
I'll get a room later.
 Slowly.

214
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:12,170
Hey, I have to meet that jerk one more time.

215
00:15:12,170 --> 00:15:14,720
Hey! Are you inside?

216
00:15:19,110 --> 00:15:22,180
Ah... No need.

217
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:25,260
Yes. I'm here.

218
00:15:30,650 --> 00:15:34,890
Just as I suspected, you're really Yoo Hyeon Jae.

219
00:15:34,890 --> 00:15:37,540
Just accept the truth now, dude.

220
00:15:37,580 --> 00:15:41,680
It doesn't feel good to hear someone much younger call me dude.

221
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:43,700
Your son thinks of me as a friend.

222
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:46,790
If he finds out I'm his dad's friend, he'll pass out.

223
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:49,880
But how come Ji Hoon doesn't look like you at all?

224
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,470
That's because...

225
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:56,020
Never mind. I don't want to talk about this with you.

226
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:59,960
So what are you going to do now? You can't stay here forever.

227
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,890
- There's no other way.
- There is another way.

228
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:05,340
You should try anything.

229
00:16:05,340 --> 00:16:07,020
What should I do?

230
00:16:07,020 --> 00:16:08,920
Let's go back to the past.

231
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:10,390
What?

232
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:22,090
Hey. I think this is only going to hurt.

233
00:16:22,090 --> 00:16:24,300
I heard from you that you slid down the stairs and you ended up coming here.

234
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:26,820
If you do exactly the same, you might go back to the past?

235
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:29,060
- I think this is too stupid.
- Stupid?

236
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:31,670
Or are you going to live here like a beggar?

237
00:16:31,670 --> 00:16:33,270
I have some money.

238
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:37,000
- What? Did you bring money with you?
- No, it's not like that.

239
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,270
